```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int findLUSlength(string a, string b) {
        if (a == b) return -1;
        return max(a.length(), b.length());
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution works by directly comparing the lengths of the two input strings. If they are equal, it means every subsequence of one string is also a subsequence of the other, so we return -1. Otherwise, we return the maximum length, which is the length of the longest uncommon subsequence. This approach has a time complexity of O(n) where n is the length of the longer string, and a space complexity of O(1) as it only uses a constant amount of space.

